[[!meta title="Sound and video"]]

Tails includes several sound and video applications:

  - **<span class="application">[Audacity](https://www.audacityteam.org/)</span>** is a multi-track audio editor
    designed for recording, playing and editing of digital audio.
    See the [official documentation](http://manual.audacityteam.org/).

  - **<span class="application">[Brasero](https://wiki.gnome.org/Apps/Brasero)</span>** is an application to burn,
    copy, and erase CD and DVD media: audio, video, or data.
    See the [official documentation](https://help.gnome.org/users/brasero/stable/).

  - **<span class="application">[Sound Juicer](https://wiki.gnome.org/Apps/SoundJuicer)</span>** is a CD
    ripper application.

  - **<span class="application">Sound Recorder</span>** is a
    simple application to record sound. Sound clips recorded using
    <span class="application">Sound Recorder</span> are saved to
    the <span class="filename">Recordings</span> folder.

  - **<span class="application">Videos</span>** is an audio and video
    player.

    For more advanced features, you can install the
    [<span class="application">VLC</span> media player](https://www.videolan.org/vlc/)
    using the [[Additional Software|doc/first_steps/additional_software]] feature.

